s cluster around the lesion (focal cortical dysplasia). (B) MEG spike sources are clustered eccentric to the lesion (low grade ganglioglioma). (C) MEG spikes sources are clustered in the middle and inferior temporal gyrus in a 5 year-old patient with intractable focal epilepsy. The spike sources are overlaid in a single axial image in all imagings. R, right; L, left; A, anterior; P, posterior.</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="kjped-56-431-g003"/></fig><table-wrap id="T1" orientation="portrait" position="float"><label>Table 1</label><caption><p>Comparison of electroencephalography (EEG) and magnetoencephalography (MEG)</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="kjped-56-431-i001"/></table-wrap></floats-group></article>